      <item>
        <title>Categories does not display items</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[mburridge]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/kasper">@kasper</a></p>
<p>CPTs should work with the existing taxonomies like <code>category</code> and <code>tag</code>. They don’t necessarily need a custom taxonomy to be defined.</p>
<p>However, when you define your CPT with <code>register_post_type</code> I think you need to define the taxonomy that it’s going to use in the <code>taxonomies</code> property in the <code>args</code> array. <a href="https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/register_post_type/">See here</a> for more info.</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/categories-does-not-display-items/4595/10">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
        <link>https://community.frontity.org/t/categories-does-not-display-items/4595/10</link>
        <pubDate>Thu, 27 May 2021 15:14:17 +0000</pubDate>
        <guid isPermaLink="false">community.frontity.org-post-4595-10</guid>
